97","g":"allow","m":"verb perfect active participle nominative plural masculine","l":"γινώσκω"},{"h":"τὴν","t":"ho","s":"G3588","g":"the","m":"article accusative singular feminine","l":"ὁ"},{"h":"ἀλήθειαν","t":"alḗtheia","s":"G225","g":"true","m":"noun accusative singular feminine","l":"ἀλήθεια"}],"flow":"The elder to the chosen lady and to her children, whom I love in truth — and not I alone, but also all those who have known the truth —","note":"GREEK: \"Presbuteros\" (πρεσβύτερος, Strong's G4245) means \"elder\" and is John's self-designation, indicating apostolic authority exercised through the office of elder. \"Eklektē kyria\" (ἐκλεκτῇ κυρίᾳ) — \"chosen lady\" — is debated: it may refer to an individual woman of prominence or, more likely, to a local congregation personified as a chosen lady, with her \"children\" being its members. THEOLOGICAL: The term \"eklektē\" (chosen/elect) carries the weight of divine election, echoing Israel's identity as God's chosen people now extended to the church (1 Pet 2:9)."},{"num":2,"words":[{"h":"διὰ","t":"diá","s":"G1223","g":"after","m":"preposition","l":"διά"},{"h":"τὴν","t":"ho","s":"G3588","g":"the","m":"article accusative singular feminine","l":"ὁ"},{"h":"ἀλήθειαν","t":"alḗtheia","s":"G225","g":"true","m":"noun accusative singular feminine","l":"ἀλήθεια"},{"h":"τὴν","t":"ho","s":"G3588","g":"the","m":"article accusative singular feminine","l":"ὁ"},{"h":"μένουσαν","t":"ménō","s":"G3306","g":"abide","m":"verb present active participle accusative singular feminine","l":"μένω"},{"h":"ἐν","t":"en","s":"G1722","g":"about","m":"preposition"},{"h":"ἡμῖν","t":"egṓ","s":"G1473","g":"I","m":"personal pronoun dative plural","l":"ἐγώ"},{"h":"καὶ","t":"kaí","s":"G2532","g":"and","m":"conjunction","l":"καί"},{"h":"μεθ’","t":"metá","s":"G3326","g":"after","m":"preposition","l":"μετά"},{"h":"ἡμῶν","t":"egṓ","s":"G1473","g":"I","m":"personal pronoun genitive plural","l":"ἐγώ"},{"h":"ἔσται","t":"eimí","s":"G1510","g":"am","m":"verb 3rd f