head and does not abide in the teaching of Christ does not have God. The one who abides in the teaching — this one has both the Father and the Son.","note":"THEOLOGICAL: \"Proagōn\" (προάγων, Strong's G4254) means \"going ahead\" or \"running ahead\" — describing those who claim progressive teaching beyond what Christ delivered. John draws a stark line: departure from the teaching of Christ means forfeiting God Himself, while abiding in that teaching secures fellowship with both Father and Son. DIVINE_COUNCIL: The inseparability of Father and Son here reflects the Johannine theology that to encounter the Son is to encounter the divine reality of the Father (John 14:9-10), affirming Christ's full participation in the divine identity."},{"num":10,"words":[{"h":"εἴ","t":"eî","s":"G1488","g":"art","m":"conjunction","l":"εἰ"},{"h":"τις","t":"tìs","s":"G5100","g":"a","m":"interrogative nominative singular masculine"},{"h":"ἔρχεται","t":"érchomai","s":"G2064","g":"accompany","m":"verb 3rd present middle indicative singular","l":"ἔρχομαι"},{"h":"πρὸς","t":"prós","s":"G4314","g":"about","m":"preposition","l":"πρός"},{"h":"ὑμᾶς","t":"sý","s":"G4771","g":"thou","m":"personal pronoun accusative plural","l":"σύ"},{"h":"καὶ","t":"kaí","s":"G2532","g":"and","m":"conjunction","l":"καί"},{"h":"ταύτην","t":"hoûtos","s":"G3778","g":"he","m":"demonstrative accusative singular feminine","l":"οὗτος"},{"h":"τὴν","t":"ho","s":"G3588","g":"the","m":"article accusative singular feminine","l":"ὁ"},{"h":"διδαχὴν","t":"didachḗ","s":"G1322","g":"doctrine","m":"noun accusative singular feminine","l":"διδαχή"},{"h":"οὐ","t":"ou","s":"G3756","g":"+ long","m":"adverb"},{"h":"φέρει","t":"phérō","s":"G5342","g":"be","m":"verb 3rd present active indicative singular","l":"φέρω"},{"h":"μὴ","t":"mḗ","s":"G3361","g":"any but","m":"adverb","l":"μή"},{"h":"λαμβάνετε","t":"lambánō","s":"G2983","g":"accept","m":"verb 2nd present active imperative plural","l":"λαμβάνω"},{"h":"αὐτὸν","t":"autós","s":"G846","g":"her","m":"personal pronoun accusative singular masculine","l":"αὐτός"},{"h":"εἰς","t":"heîs","s":"G1520","g":"a(-n","m":"preposition"},{"h":"οἰκίαν","t":"oikía","s":"G3614","g":"home","m":"noun accusative singular feminine","l":"οἰκία"},{"h":"καὶ","t":"kaí","s":"G2532","g":"and","m":"conjunction","l":"καί"},{"h":"χαίρειν","t":"chaírō","s":"G5463","g":"farewell","m":"verb present active infinitive","l":"χαίρω"},{"h":"αὐτῷ","t":"autós","s":"G846","g":"her","m":"personal pronoun dative singular masculine","l":"αὐτός"},{"h":"μὴ","t":"mḗ","s":"G3361","g":"any but","m":"adverb","l":"μή"},{"h":"λέγετε","t":"légō","s":"G3004","g":"ask","m":"verb 2nd present active imperative plural","l":"λέγω"}],"flow":"If anyone comes to you and does not bring this teaching, do not receive him into your house, and do not speak a greeting to him."},{"num":11,"words":[{"h":"ὁ","t":"ho","s":"G3588","g":"the","m":"article nominative singular masculine"},{"h":"⸂λέγων","t":"légō","s":"G3004","g":"ask","m":"verb present active participle nominative singular masculine","l":"λέγω"},{"h":"γὰρ⸃","t":"gár","s":"G1063","g":"and","m":"conjunction","l":"γάρ"},{"h":"αὐτῷ","t":"autós","s":"G846","g":"her","m":"personal pronoun dative singular masculine","l":"αὐτός"},{"h":"χαίρειν","t":"chaírō","s":"G5463","g":"farewell","m":"verb present active infinitive","l":"χαίρω"},{"h":"κοινωνεῖ","t":"koinōnéō","s":"G2841","g":"communicate","m":"verb 3rd present active indicative singular","l":"κοινωνέω"},{"h":"τοῖς","t":"ho","s":"G3588","g":"the","m":"article dative plural neuter","l":"ὁ"},{"h":"ἔργοις","t":"érgon","s":"G2041","g":"deed","m":"noun dative plural neuter","l":"ἔργον"},{"h":"αὐτοῦ","t":"autós","s":"G846","g":"her","m":"personal pronoun genitive singular masculine","l":"αὐτός"},{"h":"τοῖς","t":"ho","s":"G3588","g":"the","m":"article dative plural neuter","l":"ὁ"},{"h":"πονηροῖς","t":"ponērós","s":"G4190","g":"bad","m":"adjective dative plural neuter","l":"πονηρός"}],"flow":"For the one who speaks a greeti